      "Injured employee transported to medical facility",
      "BSEE Lafayette District conducted onsite investigation on June 06, 2014"
    ],
    "summary": "On June 05, 2014 at approximately 1400 hours, an employee was injured while attempting to check if a valve was leaking on the top of a test separator. The employee noticed a potential leak on a 1\" vent line, walked next to the vessel, and stood between two 2\" pieces of pipe. While attempting to step away from the piping after checking a valve, the employee lost his footing and came in contact with a blind flange on the process piping, resulting in two fractured ribs.",
